# Client Test Automation

Rule for automatically running client tests when client code changes.

<rule>
name: client_test_automation
description: Automatically runs client tests when client code changes
filters:
  # Match any client-side TypeScript/TSX files
  - type: file_extension
    pattern: "\\.(ts|tsx)$"
  # Match files in the client directory
  - type: path
    pattern: "^client/src/.*"
  # Match file modification events
  - type: event
    pattern: "file_modify"

actions:
  - type: suggest
    message: |
      Client code has been modified. Consider running the client tests:

      1. Run all client tests:
         ```bash
         cd client && npm test
         ```

      2. Run client tests in watch mode:
         ```bash
         cd client && npm run test:watch
         ```

      3. Run client tests with coverage:
         ```bash
         cd client && npm run test:coverage
         ```

      4. Run specific test file:
         ```bash
         cd client && npm test -- src/path/to/your.test.tsx
         ```

examples:
  - input: |
      # Modified client file
      client/src/components/Game.tsx
    output: |
      Client code has been modified. Consider running:
      cd client && npm test

metadata:
  priority: medium
  version: 1.0
  tags:
    - testing
    - client
    - automation
</rule>
